00:17:16,120 --> 00:17:21,079
Now, because we were the reason for evicting Satan from Heaven, he is out for revenge.

238
00:17:21,960 --> 00:17:26,880
So you are up against a very powerful creature, very powerful, he wanted to be a god with God.

239
00:17:27,220 --> 00:17:29,680
And we must never underestimate the power of Satan.

240
00:17:30,720 --> 00:17:32,480
So what does Satan want to do to you?

241
00:17:33,240 --> 00:17:36,799
Now that we evicted him from Heaven.

242
00:17:38,099 --> 00:17:41,359
Our father Adam was the direct cause of his eviction, at least outwardly.

243
00:17:42,519 --> 00:17:45,180
The real reason for his eviction was his rebellious thoughts.

244
00:17:45,819 --> 00:17:50,059
But Adam was the tool that was used, and he is taking out his revenge on us.

245
00:17:50,640 --> 00:17:56,859
He wants to prove to God that God indeed needs a partner.

246
00:17:57,559 --> 00:18:04,960
This is the objective he wants to prove. So his first objective is to make us disbelieve in God.

247
00:18:05,119 --> 00:18:10,619
That's his first objective. He wants you to be a disbeliever. He wants you to be an atheist.

248
00:18:12,879 --> 00:18:20,200
Now, if he fails, and you resist him, and you insist on believing in God, then his next

249
00:18:20,200 --> 00:18:25,240
attempt, which is even more formidable, is to make you a polytheist.

250
00:18:26,180 --> 00:18:30,380
If he fails in making you an atheist, he wants to make you a polytheist.

251
00:18:30,660 --> 00:18:32,579
He wants to make you an idol-worshipper.

252
00:18:33,519 --> 00:18:34,599
That's the second objective.

253
00:18:34,599 --> 00:18:45,059
If he fails in the second objective, then he works on dividing us, the believers.

254
00:18:46,380 --> 00:18:54,420
That's his last objective. And this is why in Surah 17, God says, "Tell My servants, My

255
00:18:54,420 --> 00:19:00,420
servants"—and the implication is those who believe in God and worship God alone—"to speak

256
00:19:00,420 --> 00:19:03,960
nicely to each other and treat each other in the best possible way,

257
00:19:03,960 --> 00:19:10,720
because the devil will drive a wedge between them." Now we must remember these

258
00:19:10,720 --> 00:19:15,859
three stages. The first one is to make you an atheist; if he fails, to make you a

259
00:19:15,859 --> 00:19:20,759
polytheist; if he fails, to drive a wedge between you and your brother or sister.

260
00:19:24,579 --> 00:19:29,400
Now, Alhamdulillah, we escaped the first objective; we all believe in God.

261
00:19:30,720 --> 00:19:35,039
But the majority of believers in God are going to hell, as you know, because of their idol worship.

262
00:19:37,059 --> 00:19:39,420
First of all, the majority of people will not believe.

263
00:19:40,900 --> 00:19:47,759
So, Satan, to some extent, succeeded in duping the majority of people into being atheists, disbelievers.

264
00:19:47,759 --> 00:19:52,579
And then he duped the majority of believers into being idolatrous.

265
00:19:56,460 --> 00:20:01,839
The third objective is to divide us and make us dislike each other.

266
00:20:04,500 --> 00:20:06,319
Now, we must make him pay.

267
00:20:09,640 --> 00:20:14,339
As a group of people who succeeded in escaping the first trap

268
00:20:14,339 --> 00:20:20,000
and the second set of traps, we must work on the third trap.

269
00:20:21,160 --> 00:20:26,440
We must never have a hard feeling, or a dislike towards a brother or a sister.

270
00:20:28,599 --> 00:20:35,759
And when I finish this khutbah, and sit down to repent, I want you all, you and me,

271
00:20:35,920 --> 00:20:42,700
to direct this repentance to the wedges that Satan may have driven between you and me,

272
00:20:42,700 --> 00:20:44,119
or you and a brother, or you and a sister.

273
00:20:46,559 --> 00:20:47,960
And the way to do it,

274
00:20:48,659 --> 00:20:50,480
is to absolutely forget the past.

275
00:20:53,720 --> 00:20:56,400
As if you are meeting the person for the first time in your life.

276
00:20:57,339 --> 00:20:58,720
You concentrate on that.

277
00:20:59,700 --> 00:21:00,460
Now, let's suppose.

278
00:21:00,759 --> 00:21:02,420
So Wali and I, we have...

279
00:21:02,420 --> 00:21:04,759
Satan has succeeded in driving a wedge between us.

280
00:21:05,339 --> 00:21:07,539
Then when we sit down to repent, I'm going to say,

281
00:21:08,699 --> 00:21:10,500
"I'll forget everything Wali did to me,

282
00:21:10,500 --> 00:21:15,140
anything bad, and I'm going to meet

283
00:21:15,140 --> 00:21:16,079
Wali for the first time."

284
00:21:16,200 --> 00:21:18,160
As if he's new to me for the first time.

285
00:21:18,500 --> 00:22:07,279
When you come out of this repentance, I want you to think of any person you don't like, in this room, or outside, any of the believers. As if you're going to meet him for the first time. So you come, if you have anything against me, I want this thought to come over you: "I am going to treat him as if I never met him before." As far as his words are concerned, or any bad actions he has done against me. It is very important that we succeed in this, because any success he obtains is detrimental to us. And this is his last trap. You must convince yourself that you are meeting this person for the first time. So, my name is Rashad, and your name is Wali, now, we have nothing against each other, because we're meeting for the first time.

301
00:22:17,119 --> 00:22:23,119
Satan will drive wedges among the people, so when they go in, they will not say salam alaykum to each other, or greet each other.

302
00:22:23,559 --> 00:22:32,259
But if the person we're meeting is a person for the first time, so we're going to make today a day of renewal, of wholeness.

303
00:22:32,259 --> 00:22:40,099
If you have anybody you don't like, when this prayer is over and you're meeting that person for the first time,

304
00:22:40,279 --> 00:22:42,039
we must give each other a chance.

305
00:22:44,720 --> 00:22:51,839
Give your brother and sister a chance. I mean, no mistake is so gross that it cannot be forgiven.

306
00:22:52,400 --> 00:22:57,700
Now, the Quran repeats over and over that you must forgive and forget.

307
00:23:01,239 --> 00:23:09,579
So let us give each other a chance and start all over again, for a hard feeling we shouldn't have.

308
00:23:12,079 --> 00:23:19,720
So we are going to sit down and we are going to repent for letting Satan succeed in driving wedges between any of us.

309
00:23:20,980 --> 00:23:24,299
And we are going to pledge that he will never succeed again, we will never let him.

310
00:23:24,299 --> 00:23:26,980
We're going to treat each other in the nicest possible way.

311
00:23:27,599 --> 00:23:31,480
We're going to talk to each other, treat each other in the nicest possible way.

312
00:23:31,500 --> 00:23:32,720
This is a commandment from God.

313
00:23:33,759 --> 00:23:37,099
Tell my servants to treat each other in the best possible way

314
00:23:37,099 --> 00:23:38,960
and to utter the nicest words.

315
00:23:40,359 --> 00:23:42,200
The word 'utter' is in the verse.

316
00:23:43,819 --> 00:23:47,720
For Satan will try to drive a wedge between them.

317
00:23:49,019 --> 00:23:52,319
And when this prayer is over, we're going to be the most loving group in the world,

318
00:23:52,319 --> 00:23:53,779
as we are always supposed to be.

319
00:23:54,140 --> 00:23:55,259
So the Quran says,

320
00:23:55,700 --> 00:23:57,039
إِنَّمَا الْمُؤْمِنُونَ إِخْوَةٌ

321
00:23:57,039 --> 00:23:59,519
The believers are one family.

322
00:24:00,140 --> 00:24:00,579
Brethren.

323
00:24:01,799 --> 00:24:02,240
Siblings.

324
00:24:03,420 --> 00:24:05,599
Whatever the translation is, it includes male and female.

325
00:24:06,319 --> 00:24:08,539
We are, this is your family, you know.

326
00:24:09,359 --> 00:24:09,960
Because your

327
00:24:09,960 --> 00:24:12,019
blood family, your genetic family

328
00:24:12,019 --> 00:24:13,299
may not go with you to heaven.

329
00:24:15,500 --> 00:24:16,480
But this family,

330
00:24:16,539 --> 00:24:17,779
the people who believe in God alone,

331
00:24:18,039 --> 00:24:19,680
you're going to be stuck with us forever.

332
00:24:22,759 --> 00:24:32,619
So this is the real family. Millions of years. Your genetic family is yours for 60 years or 70 years.

333
00:24:33,980 --> 00:24:39,740
But your spiritual family is your family for eternity. And we must maintain the best possible relationships.

334
00:24:40,180 --> 00:24:43,940
And when we repent, we are going to be full of love for Allah. SubhanAllah. Repent.

335
00:24:54,539 --> 00:24:59,200
Think of anyone you have any grudge against, and forget that grudge, forgive and forget.

336
00:25:03,920 --> 00:25:06,940
Then you treat those people as if you are meeting them for the first time,

337
00:25:11,940 --> 00:25:15,460
Alhamdulillah, wa ashadu an la ilaha illa Allah, wa atubu ilayh.

338
00:25:19,180 --> 00:25:21,240
There is a verse in Surah Al-Zumar that says,

339
00:25:24,880 --> 00:25:31,099
Tell my servants who exceeded the limits, or crossed the limits,

340
00:25:33,820 --> 00:25:40,880
Do not, never despair from the mercy of God, for God forgives all sins.

341
00:25:43,340 --> 00:25:44,160
That's one of the

342
00:25:44,200 --> 00:25:45,700
most beautiful verses in the Quran.

343
00:25:47,480 --> 00:25:49,940
There's only one offense.

344
00:25:50,259 --> 00:25:52,259
The greatest sin is to be an idol worshiper.

345
00:25:52,539 --> 00:25:53,859
It's much greater than that.

346
00:25:55,920 --> 00:26:01,799
And in this Masjid, you know, we read the total elimination of idol worship.

347
00:26:02,740 --> 00:26:08,819
I was talking about the greatness of God. We all realize that only God can benefit you or harm you.

348
00:26:09,620 --> 00:26:20,440
And that if you ever think that anything or anyone or any material can benefit you or harm you in any way, then you have fallen in idol worship.

349
00:26:21,299 --> 00:26:25,500
You must know that God controls the flow of every single blood cell in your body.

350
00:26:25,880 --> 00:26:31,960
How it flows, where it is going, how much sustenance you deserve, how much health you

351
00:26:31,960 --> 00:26:35,960
deserve, how much money is good for you.

352
00:26:37,539 --> 00:26:39,180
Money is not always good for you.

353
00:26:40,460 --> 00:26:43,240
God decides all this and we recognize that.

354
00:26:45,039 --> 00:26:50,099
But if you ever think that Jesus or Mary or Muhammad or Hussain or Ali or anybody can

355
00:26:50,440 --> 00:26:54,559
benefit you, or harm you, or anything, you have fallen into idol worship.

356
00:26:55,180 --> 00:26:57,140
You think your job provides you with money.

357
00:26:58,259 --> 00:27:00,380
You have fallen into idol worship.

358
00:27:01,480 --> 00:27:02,980
You must have God in mind.

359
00:27:05,940 --> 00:27:09,420
The only thing that is not forgivable, as it is repeated in the Quran,

360
00:27:09,619 --> 00:27:10,980
there are two verses in Surah 4.

361
00:27:11,880 --> 00:27:14,019
إِنَّ ٱللَّهَ لَا يَغْفِرُ أَن يُشْرَكَ بِهِ

362
00:27:14,019 --> 00:27:17,759
God does not forgive that you set up idols.

363
00:27:22,379 --> 00:27:23,920
That's the only unforgivable offense.

364
00:27:25,099 --> 00:27:33,119
Now this mosque is internationally famous, as we were told yesterday, for saying that

365
00:27:33,119 --> 00:27:36,059
Hadith is bad, and Sunnah is bad.

366
00:27:36,200 --> 00:27:39,059
You cannot follow Hadith and Sunnah; they actually have nothing to do with the Prophet.

367
00:27:40,240 --> 00:27:44,180
We believe God when He says the Quran is complete, perfect, and fully detailed.

368
00:27:47,099 --> 00:27:52,500
Now, the biggest accusation against us in Masjid Tucson is that we disrespect the Prophet.

369
00:27:55,659 --> 00:27:57,440
Right? No, the accusation is rife.

370
00:28:01,279 --> 00:28:05,819
Of course we don't disrespect the Prophet. We realize he is the final Prophet, the Messenger of God.

371
00:28:06,079 --> 00:28:11,000
He was chosen to utter the last words of God. We know that. But you know he is dead, he can't help us.

372
00:28:11,000 --> 00:28:15,559
His sole mission was the delivery. And we know that the hadith and sunnah have nothing to do with him.

373
00:28:16,359 --> 00:28:19,720
But you see, Satan fabricated those things, as the Quran teaches us.

374
00:28:20,019 --> 00:28:24,200
Satan fabricated, he said, the Prophet said. Satan said, the Prophet said.

375
00:28:24,339 --> 00:28:28,779
And they are falling on their faces in Satan's trap.

376
00:28:29,220 --> 00:28:32,160
But what I want to say is, let us agree with them.

377
00:28:32,640 --> 00:28:35,440
Let us say we disrespect the Prophet. The question is,

378
00:28:37,859 --> 00:28:39,539
is disrespecting the Prophet forgivable?

379
00:28:40,640 --> 00:28:48,380
Is murder forgivable? Is adultery forgivable? Is lying forgivable? Is cheating forgivable?

380
00:28:48,759 --> 00:28:50,539
The verse of Surah Az-Zumar says,

381
00:28:51,460 --> 00:28:58,079
"Say, 'O My servants who have transgressed against their own souls, never despair of the mercy of God, for God forgives all sins.'"

382
00:28:59,019 --> 00:29:02,579
And throughout the Quran, the only unforgivable offense is idol worship.

383
00:29:06,019 --> 00:29:12,500
So, just to avoid idol worship, which is not forgivable, and to fall into disrespect of

384
00:29:12,500 --> 00:29:18,519
the Prophet, which we don't, but even that, that is forgivable, but idol worship is not.

385
00:29:18,920 --> 00:29:21,099
And we don't want to be idol worshipers.

386
00:29:27,500 --> 00:29:32,240
You know, the choice: disrespecting the Prophet versus idol worship.

387
00:29:35,619 --> 00:29:38,980
And if we have to choose, what would you choose?

388
00:29:39,039 --> 00:29:40,799
Idol worship or disrespecting the Prophet?

389
00:29:41,400 --> 00:29:42,859
We do not disrespect the Prophet.

390
00:29:43,160 --> 00:29:48,240
We know exactly who he is, what he is, what he stands for, what he wants, what he wishes.

391
00:29:49,159 --> 00:29:51,740
Just like you. You wish all the people to be believers.

392
00:29:52,779 --> 00:29:55,579
And so do Muhammad, and Jesus, and Mary; they are all the same.

393
00:29:56,799 --> 00:30:00,059
That's what they want. They don't want us to idolize them.

394
00:30:00,579 --> 00:30:04,200
They want us to worship God. This is why in the Surah

395
00:30:04,200 --> 00:30:08,240
of the Prophets, one of the important verses says, "We did not send

396
00:30:08,240 --> 00:30:12,079
any messenger before you except to inspire him

397
00:30:12,079 --> 00:30:16,140
that: 'There is no god except Me, so worship Me.'"

398
00:30:20,220 --> 00:30:27,980
We did not send any messenger except to give one and the same message, which is,

399
00:30:27,980 --> 00:30:28,480
"There is no god but God."

400
00:30:32,500 --> 00:30:37,460
So, saints, prophets, and Mary and Jesus, they also benefit us naught.

401
00:30:38,559 --> 00:30:41,640
And then, you've wasted your life.

402
00:30:45,799 --> 00:30:50,640
So even if they accuse you of disrespecting the Prophet, and it's your word against theirs.

403
00:30:50,640 --> 00:30:55,319
They say you disrespect the Prophet; you say, "No, I respect the Prophet." It is as Abdullah said,

404
00:30:55,960 --> 00:30:56,400
instinctive.

405
00:30:57,240 --> 00:30:58,640
You don't disrespect the Prophet.

406
00:30:58,980 --> 00:31:01,980
If they insist, you say to them, "Well, that's idol worship, and that's unforgivable."

407
00:31:07,119 --> 00:31:12,559
We must never let Satan sneak any kind of idol worship into our hearts, our minds.

408
00:31:14,720 --> 00:31:18,359
We must always be aware of the greatness of God, that He is the doer of everything.

409
00:31:22,940 --> 00:31:30,079
And when we enter our prayers, we do a deliberate act of humbling ourselves before our Creator.

410
00:31:30,079 --> 00:31:34,019
In the name of God, the Most Gracious, the Most Merciful.

411
00:31:37,440 --> 00:31:39,940
May God bless you.
